<h1 style="text-align:center; color:#000066">Jesus' Message #25<br>
April 14, 2011</h1>

<p>My dearest children, I am Jesus, the beloved of God, who comes unto you from the Father to share the message of His all-encompassing love. How has love come to be something that is foreign to you? For some, the message seems too much; it seems too high a standard up to which to live. Have I not commanded you to be perfect (Matthew 5:48)? My children, you are made of the very love, the very essence, of God the Father, for you are in His image and likeness. Therefore, reject not the message, for your purpose can be nothing else but to live out your true nature, to express your true essence here upon earth.</p>

<p>Within every one of you, there is a spark of light, even a flame, so dazzling and radiant as to blind the physical eyes if it could be seen. Within every one of you is the spark from the Creator of your souls, which has always been of His essence, and  will always be of His essence, no matter what covering is placed over it. However, I tell you this truly, it is impossible to cover the light of God forever. Think not that the path is too difficult to tread upon, for it is an inevitable path that every soul will tread upon in time, whenever they are ready. It is not an adding to, but a falling away. Nothing can be added to your soul, for it is already perfect in truth and essence. Only that which is not true must be taken away.</p>

<p>That which is not true can only harm you, though you cling onto it like it were your very life. Only that which is real can bring life, and that which is real is God, and God alone. No physical, mental, or emotional object can bring any sustenance whatsoever, and if focused upon with great appetite, forgetting to be filled by the presence of God, will lead to further separation and destruction.</p>

<p>I have told you that the way to the Kingdom is through forgiveness, and acceptance of the great love of God for you, which is and has always been there. However, it is as though you are blind to it, so enamored are you with the things in this world. Ah, if you would only seek the inner light, the flame within, that divine spark which leads directly to its Source, God, then you would see how foolish your previous existence has been, and you would fully embrace the love and the light of God with happiness and bliss.</p>

<p>For I tell you, you lack nothing, but only imagine that you do so. I tell you that within you, in your essence, is the full glory of God, and His full authority within this universe, for what is of God cannot be of a different nature entirely, and must possess the same powers as that from which it comes. For light comes from light, glory from glory, love from love, power from great power, but only those who realize their coronation as true sons and daughters of God, yea as the Living God Himself, should come into full mastery over themselves and over that which once had power over them. Marvel not at the mastery I displayed upon earth over the elements, over the weather, over sickness, and even over death itself. I tell you that this is no supernatural gift, but is the inheritance of all who accept their power in the essence of God. This is the inherent power of the Christ within you, whom you are truly. You have merely given up that power for a time, because you believed that lesser things had greater worth. Reverse that thinking now, and you would return to your true nature, taking it up fully in service to all.</p>

